      "content": "thanks for the info on de jure sovereignty. it really feels like that's the key here. since the sovereignty was never actually signed away, just stolen by force, the legitimacy of my claim remains intact despite what modern maps show. \n\nif i want to move from just \"researching\" to actually establishing a presence, i need to treat this like a real diplomatic mission. what are the first practical steps a legitimate sovereign would take to gain international recognition? should i be looking into establishing a formal diplomatic mission or maybe seeking consultative status with an international body to present my family's evidence?",
